sentences.english: Ageing will put pressure on societies at all levels.
sentences.chinese: 老齡問題將對社會各階層帶來壓力。

sentences.english: The acids in tomato juice can degrade the drink’s other ingredients.
sentences.chinese: 番茄汁中的酸會削弱其他材料帶來的味覺。

sentences.english: Hideyoshi himself brought along two portable teahouses in starkly contrasting styles.
sentences.chinese: 豐臣秀吉本人帶來了兩個風格截然不同的便攜式茶館。

sentences.english: That was Hedwig. She brought a letter from Lupin .
sentences.chinese: 是海德薇，她帶來了一封盧平的信。

sentences.english: Quality and moderation often bring more joy than an excess.
sentences.chinese: 品質和適度通常會比超額帶來更多的歡樂。

sentences.english: EA brings MONOPOLY's new card game to mobile.
sentences.chinese: 電子藝界壟斷帶來的新遊戲移動。

sentences.english: They are round and so they bring us good luck all the year round.
sentences.chinese: 它們都是圓的，能給我們帶來一年的好運氣。

sentences.english: Hooley 's Irish Pub brings an authentic slice of Irish culture to Guangzhou.
sentences.chinese: 胡利的愛爾蘭酒吧給廣州帶來了真正的愛爾蘭文化片。

sentences.english: I say that because it gives tremendous liquidity to the markets.
sentences.chinese: 我這樣說是因爲它給市場帶來的巨大的流動性。

sentences.english: Rewards for past good deeds will be yours.
sentences.chinese: 往時的善事會給帶來報答。

sentences.english: Trouble develops, however, when any human instinct or appetite causes overdeveloped.
sentences.chinese: 但假使人的欲求或喜好過度膨脹則會帶來麻煩。

sentences.english: Chinese government is popular with the people because the government brings stability and wealth to the people.
sentences.chinese: 中國政府卻因爲爲人民帶來了穩定和財富而深得民心。

sentences.english: Bottom line, you bring in revenue for them, you win, they win.
sentences.chinese: 底線就是，你爲他們帶來收入，大家雙贏。

sentences.english: Music brings my heart fairy air.
Shi Xing pain Chen interests, points out the consequences of the Japanese occupation of Korea will bring.
sentences.chinese: 石星痛陳利害，指出了日軍佔領朝鮮會帶來的惡果。

sentences.english: Papa would bring an old battered coal shovel and an old-fashioned ice chest with him.
sentences.chinese: 爺爺總會帶來一把破舊的煤鏟和一臺老式冰櫃。
